To demonstrate real-time file synchronization between host and container.
On the host system, create a directory named webdata.
Inside it, create a file index.html with the content:
     <h1>Welcome from Host</h1>
Run an Nginx container and bind mount the host directory to
/usr/share/nginx/html using --mount.
Expose the container on port 8080.
Open a browser and verify the page loads.
Modify index.html on the host to:
<h1>Updated from Host</h1>
Refresh the browser and observe the change.
cmd= PS C:\docker\website> mkdir C:\webdata

    Directory: C:\

Mode                 LastWriteTime         Length Name
----                 -------------         ------ ----
d----          17-02-2026    18:58                webdata

PS C:\docker\website> notepad C:\webdata\index.html
PS C:\docker\website> docker run -d --name web_sync `--mount type=bind,source=C:\webdata,target=/usr/share/nginx/html `-p 8080:80 nginx
